  "response_text": "A group of office workers stands in a beige conference room with patterned carpet, name badges, and wall sconces, as if attending a team-building workshop. A slim, curly blond facilitator in a vest gestures toward a middle-aged man in a blue button-down shirt with a badge clipped to his chest. The man looks tense and unsmiling. He folds his arms across his chest, braces himself, and then is seen lying flat on the carpet in the middle of the room while other participants stand around him, suggesting a trust-fall exercise that has not gone comfortably.\n\nThe workshop continues with people paired off in rows, standing extremely close together. The man in the blue shirt is face-to-face with another man in a red plaid shirt; their noses are nearly touching, and both stand stiffly with strained expressions. Around them, other pairs of coworkers are just as close, filling the room in an awkward exercise about personal space.\n\nThe man in blue steps away to a refreshment area inside the same conference space, holding a phone to his ear and gripping the strap of a shoulder bag. Behind him are coffee urns, cups, and other attendees milling around. As he talks, he glances sideways and over his shoulder. A man in a short-sleeved plaid shirt holding a cup looks toward him, as if noticing what he is saying.\n\nBack with the group, the man in blue is now wearing an exaggerated tall black top hat. In white capital letters across the front, the hat reads “HONESTY.” He stands in the center of the room with a resigned, embarrassed expression while the other participants form a semicircle behind him. The blond facilitator stands beside him with one hand on his shoulder, her mouth open as if addressing the group. The man looks down and then forward, still wearing the oversized hat, while the surrounding coworkers watch.\n\nThe pressure escalates: the man sits or stands tightly surrounded by coworkers leaning in from every side. A tower of small wooden blocks is stacked directly in front of him, like a game or exercise prop. People crowd his face with objects, including a white cup or bottle, an orange cone-shaped item, and a red marker or pen. He keeps his eyes down and his face closed off, looking trapped and uncomfortable as the group presses in close.\n\nThe setting changes to a bright airport interior. The same man, still in his blue shirt and carrying his shoulder bag, is bent forward while holding a phone to his ear. In his other hand he clutches a small gray object shaped like an airplane. A man in the background, wearing a plaid shirt and carrying a dark folder, stands near a wall and looks in his direction. The man on the phone turns his head, then moves off quickly.\n\nAt an airport gate, the man hurries alongside another man in a dark suit. They approach a doorway marked by a large overhead sign. A white-haired woman in a dark airline uniform stands by the entrance, smiling and extending a hand in greeting. The gate sign on the left reads “K19.” To its right, a black digital display with yellow-green text first reads, “Making your escape.” As the man reaches the gate, the display updates to “Making your escape. Sooner.”\n\nThe final images show the side of a shiny American Airlines airplane under a wing, with blue sky and clouds behind it. Bright sunlight glints across the silver fuselage, partially washing over the large red “American” lettering. A blue stripe with rows of oval windows runs along the side of the plane, with red and blue trim below. In the upper left corner, white on-screen text appears as “AA.com,” identifying the airline’s website.",
